m) Using a left join, count the number of movies by genre, and display the counts only where they are greater than or equal to 20. Order the results from the highest counts to the lowest

SELECT genres.genre_name, COUNT(movies_genres.genre_id) AS movie_count
FROM genres
LEFT JOIN movies_genres ON genres.genre_id = movies_genres.genre_id
GROUP BY genres.genre_name
HAVING movie_count>=20
ORDER BY movie_count DESC

c) Add a column mainspecies to the starwars data set which has the value of species where num>1, and ‘Other’ if num is 1

starwars <- starwars %>%
  mutate(mainspecies = case_when(
    num > 1 ~ as.character(species),
    num == 1 ~ "Other"
  ))

d) Use ggplot to draw a scatter plot of the height and mass variables. Colour the points by mainspecies.

ggplot(starwars) + 
  geom_point(aes(x = height, y = mass, colour = mainspecies), position = "jitter")

# Storing the two species "humans" and "droids" in vectors 
Human <- no_jabba %>% filter(species == "Human")
Droid <- no_jabba %>% filter(species == "Droid")

plot_1 <- ggplot(Human, aes(x = height, y = mass)) + 
  geom_point() +
